description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Physics Equipment Management Service (MPEMS) requires one dynamic medical equipment Maintenance Support Worker, to take a key role within the service. This is a demanding position and you will play a major part in achieving service objectives in a busy and technically challenging environment governed by an ISO9001 quality system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have the ability to self manage and prioritise the direction of their day to day activities to achieve timely completion of all maintenance and associated support tasks. The role is performed both in-house and at various customer sites throughout Leicestershire. A driving licence is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have obtained a relevant apprentice Level 2 qualification, and it is desirable that you have previous knowledge of working in a workshop environment. Training will be available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a safety conscious approach to your work and the ability to communicate effectively with people at all levels. An ability to cope under pressure, be adaptable and multi-task is required. Experience of using a database and associated IT skills will be a distinct advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carl Bond - Lead Clinical Technologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;carl.bond@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0116 258 6840&lt;/p&gt;
